Debounce: jalankan function hanya setelah tidak ada call baru selama X ms. Berguna untuk search input, resize handler, dll.

```javascript
/**
 * Debounce — tunggu X ms setelah call terakhir sebelum eksekusi.
 * @param {Function} fn - Function yang ingin di-debounce
 * @param {number} delay - Delay dalam ms
 * @param {Object} options
 * @param {boolean} options.leading - Jalankan juga di awal (default: false)
 * @returns {Function}
 */
function debounce(fn, delay, { leading = false } = {}) {
  let timer = null;
  let hasCalledLeading = false;

  return function (...args) {
    const context = this;

    if (leading && !timer) {
      fn.apply(context, args);
      hasCalledLeading = true;
    }

    clearTimeout(timer);
    timer = setTimeout(() => {
      if (!leading || !hasCalledLeading) {
        fn.apply(context, args);
      }
      timer = null;
      hasCalledLeading = false;
    }, delay);
  };
}

// Contoh pakai di React:
const handleSearch = debounce((query) => {
  fetch(`/api/search?q=${query}`).then(/*...*/);
}, 300);

// Event listener:
const input = document.querySelector('#search');
input.addEventListener('input', (e) => handleSearch(e.target.value));
```

**Versi modern dengan AbortController (cancel request juga):**
```javascript
function useSearch() {
  let controller = null;
  const search = debounce(async (query) => {
    controller?.abort();
    controller = new AbortController();
    try {
      const resp = await fetch(`/api/search?q=${query}`, { signal: controller.signal });
      return await resp.json();
    } catch (e) {
      if (e.name !== 'AbortError') throw e;
    }
  }, 300);
  return search;
}
```

Perbedaan debounce vs throttle: debounce = tunggu berhenti, throttle = maksimum N kali per detik.

Pattern untuk type-safe API response di TypeScript:

```typescript
// Result type — explicit success/error tanpa try-catch
type Result<T, E = Error> =
  | { ok: true; data: T }
  | { ok: false; error: E };

// API error types
interface ApiError {
  status: number;
  message: string;
  code?: string;
}

// Generic fetch helper
async function apiFetch<T>(
  url: string,
  options?: RequestInit
): Promise<Result<T, ApiError>> {
  try {
    const resp = await fetch(url, {
      ...options,
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        ...options?.headers,
      },
    });

    if (!resp.ok) {
      const body = await resp.json().catch(() => ({}));
      return {
        ok: false,
        error: { status: resp.status, message: body.detail ?? resp.statusText },
      };
    }

    const data: T = await resp.json();
    return { ok: true, data };
  } catch (e) {
    return {
      ok: false,
      error: { status: 0, message: e instanceof Error ? e.message : 'Network error' },
    };
  }
}

// Domain types
interface Proposal {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  problem: string;
  risk_level: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high' | 'critical';
  stage: string;
  creator_verdict: 'approved' | 'rejected' | null;
  created_at: string;
}

interface ProposalList {
  total: number;
  items: Proposal[];
}

// Pakai:
const result = await apiFetch<ProposalList>('/v1/sandbox/proposals');

if (!result.ok) {
  console.error(`Error ${result.error.status}: ${result.error.message}`);
  return;
}

result.data.items.forEach(p => {
  console.log(p.title, p.risk_level);  // Fully typed!
});
```

Pola ini (Result type) menghilangkan silent failures — caller dipaksa handle error case secara eksplisit. Dipakai di Rust, Go, dan semakin populer di TypeScript modern.

